      <hedline>
        <hl1>Watching the Grass Grow</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Jonathan D Reichman letter on May 18 article on robotic lawnmowers</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>''Pull Up a Lawn Chair and Watch the Robot Mow the Grass'' (May 18) called to mind Jerry Lewis being chased by an army of robotic lawnmowers in the 1962 comedy ''It's Only Money.'' This is one invention I'll steer clear of (no pun intended).  JONATHAN  D. REICHMAN  Chappaqua, N.Y.</p>
      </block>
